<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870806-0005 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Philadelphia Electric Co.</HL><DD> 08/06/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PE </IN><TEXT>   An administrative law judge for the Pennsylvania Public Utility Commission has recommended that Philadelphia Electric Co. refund $5.5 million to customers for the cost of replacement power during outages at the Salem, N.J., and Peach Bottom nuclear power plants. The Peach Bottom plant is in Delta, Pa. The recommendation, which cites &quot;imprudent&quot; management decisions during the outages, requires approval from the commission before the utility must comply. </TEXT></DOC>